00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,230
You're really fair-skinned.

873
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:35,110
Is it hereditary?

874
00:30:35,110 --> 00:30:35,520
Yeah.

875
00:30:35,520 --> 00:30:36,280
Your parents too?

876
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:36,830
Yeah.

877
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:40,470
Born with fair skin.

878
00:30:45,950 --> 00:30:46,990
What are you trying to say?

879
00:30:48,830 --> 00:30:50,640
You could make your kid
fair-skinned too.

880
00:30:58,230 --> 00:30:59,800
Knew you'd bring up something like that.

881
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:01,330
I wasn't going to

882
00:31:01,830 --> 00:31:03,760
say it窶ｦ but since you insisted.

883
00:31:04,430 --> 00:31:06,230
I said it, which sounds too cheesy.

884
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,190
Why are you driving so slowly?

885
00:31:15,070 --> 00:31:15,710
Keep it steady.

886
00:31:15,710 --> 00:31:16,800
We've still got folks

887
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,680
sleeping soundly.

888
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:19,390
That's the reason?

889
00:31:19,830 --> 00:31:20,160
Nope.

890
00:31:21,830 --> 00:31:23,310
I just want time to move slower.

891
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:31,230
Where's the band-aid?

892
00:31:31,230 --> 00:31:32,030
My wound's healed.

893
00:31:32,030 --> 00:31:33,230
Still haven't got the band-aid.

894
00:31:34,230 --> 00:31:35,430
My brain's all over the place.

895
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:40,190
Knock it awake.

896
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:43,110
What are you even doing?

897
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:45,070
I've no idea either.

898
00:31:45,590 --> 00:31:46,230
What am I doing?

899
00:31:46,880 --> 00:31:47,800
What am I even doing?

900
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,350
Calm down for a second.

901
00:32:01,230 --> 00:32:03,110
I feel like you've changed a lot.

902
00:32:03,470 --> 00:32:05,430
I'm someone who needs to be

903
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:07,640
opened up by someone,

904
00:32:08,520 --> 00:32:08,950
you know?

905
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:11,760
Was it me or did you do it yourself?

906
00:32:12,710 --> 00:32:13,680
It was you.

907
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,070
I could never do it on my own.

908
00:32:23,830 --> 00:32:25,040
笙ｪBaby笙ｪ

909
00:32:26,190 --> 00:32:27,400
笙ｪBaby笙ｪ

910
00:32:28,070 --> 00:32:28,640
Who?

911
00:32:29,070 --> 00:32:32,160
笙ｪYou'll always be my baby笙ｪ

912
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:34,590
笙ｪBaby笙ｪ

913
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,110
笙ｪBaby笙ｪ

914
00:32:37,950 --> 00:32:38,800
At that moment,

915
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:40,380
my heart was fluttering like crazy.

916
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:42,680
I was really happy, but also super shy.

917
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,280
It brought me much closer

918
00:32:44,280 --> 00:32:45,230
to Enda.

919
00:32:46,710 --> 00:32:47,680
Here we are, baby.

920
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:54,350
We're here, baby.

921
00:32:55,110 --> 00:32:55,920
So sleepy.

922
00:33:01,760 --> 00:33:02,470
Let's go.

923
00:33:05,830 --> 00:33:07,070
Thank you.

924
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:09,880
Hello.

925
00:33:11,710 --> 00:33:12,280
Could you窶ｦ

926
00:33:12,280 --> 00:33:14,040
help grab something from the (car)?

927
00:33:14,310 --> 00:33:15,230
There's more, right?

928
00:33:15,230 --> 00:33:16,310
Yeah, on that (car).

929
00:33:16,310 --> 00:33:18,040
Let the guys go get it.

930
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:19,310
Go on, guys, we handle it.

931
00:33:19,310 --> 00:33:20,920
Come on, guys, let's move.

932
00:33:21,590 --> 00:33:22,280
Let's head back.

933
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:24,190
I'll walk her back to her room.

934
00:33:27,310 --> 00:33:28,110
Where's my clothes?

935
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:30,310
Can you fetch it for me?

936
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:31,950
Or you could take them now.

937
00:33:31,950 --> 00:33:32,640
Come with us.

938
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:33,760
Me?

939
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:34,400
Yes.

940
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:34,880
No.

941
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:35,560
Why not?

942
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:36,920
Why not?

943
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:38,280
Then I'll fetch it later.

944
00:33:38,610 --> 00:33:39,520
It doesn't sound great.

945
00:33:39,520 --> 00:33:41,190
It'd be embarrassing if someone saw us.

946
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:43,190
What's wrong with you?

947
00:33:44,580 --> 00:33:45,560
Heading back to the dorm?

948
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:46,710
Then I'll fetch it for you.

949
00:33:47,110 --> 00:33:47,800
Then wait a sec.

950
00:33:49,590 --> 00:33:50,110
Hey, beauty.

951
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:51,880
Just give it to Yang.

952
00:33:52,350 --> 00:33:53,280
Me?

953
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:54,690
So there's a "passing down", right?

954
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,160
Yeah, exactly.

955
00:33:58,350 --> 00:33:59,520
Great, I'm Steve again.

956
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:00,590
Steve?

957
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:01,350
Forget it.

958
00:34:01,350 --> 00:34:02,160
If I'm Steve,

959
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:02,640
so be it.

960
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:04,040
My feet are soaked.

961
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:06,400
I'm definitely Steve.

962
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:07,280
Always Steve.

963
00:34:12,710 --> 00:34:13,470
Enda.

964
00:34:13,470 --> 00:34:14,520
I'll be back in a minute.

965
00:34:15,430 --> 00:34:19,390
笙ｪLove feels like drifting sand笙ｪ

966
00:34:19,390 --> 00:34:21,230
笙ｪI won't fight against it笙ｪ

967
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,900
I'm speechless.

968
00:34:23,900 --> 00:34:24,630
What should I do?

969
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:27,120
Guan is way too passive.

970
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:28,280
That's just how he is.

971
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,380
Is this your first day knowing him?

972
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:31,520
But I'm passive too.

973
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:32,280
I don't like this.

974
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:33,040
Well?

975
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:35,000
Anything we can work on?

976
00:34:35,390 --> 00:34:35,950
What is this?

977
00:34:35,950 --> 00:34:37,560
I'll go make myself some noodles first.

978
00:34:37,560 --> 00:34:38,870
I'm starving to death here.

979
00:34:38,870 --> 00:34:39,870
Haven't had lunch yet.

980
00:34:40,390 --> 00:34:41,040
I'm boiling mad.

981
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:41,560
At him.

982
00:34:42,470 --> 00:34:43,800
Because he's not that caring?

983
00:34:44,190 --> 00:34:46,120
Yeah, especially compared to Enda.

984
00:34:46,390 --> 00:34:47,800
We've known each other way longer.

985
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:48,190
And...

986
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:49,080
Longer in what way?

987
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:50,120
It's just a more few days.

988
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:52,120
Because I left the island the second day.

989
00:34:52,120 --> 00:34:53,150
Girl.

990
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:54,950
One extra day.

991
00:34:54,950 --> 00:34:55,600
Two days.

992
00:34:56,430 --> 00:34:58,080
I even spent the whole day with him.

993
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:58,870
On a date.

994
00:34:59,670 --> 00:35:01,360
What's that supposed to mean?

995
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,390
I'm seriously mad now.

996
00:35:04,390 --> 00:35:05,670
I'm not talking to him.

997
00:35:06,190 --> 00:35:07,390
I'll head out. He's waiting.

998
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:11,430
Village Chief, your clothes.

999
00:35:12,150 --> 00:35:13,710
It's a bit messy.

1000
00:35:13,710 --> 00:35:14,630
Some lint stuck to it.

1001
00:35:14,630 --> 00:35:15,360
Right.

1002
00:35:20,520 --> 00:35:22,360
Guan, Yan is still in the room.

1003
00:35:22,670 --> 00:35:23,560
In the room?

1004
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:24,280
What she's doing?

1005
00:35:25,120 --> 00:35:26,120
Fixing her hair.

1006
00:35:26,670 --> 00:35:27,320
Why so long?

1007
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:28,120
I'll check on her.

1008
00:35:28,580 --> 00:35:31,860
(Protecting her sister's happiness,
keeping the credit hidden).

1009
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:33,080
Yan.

1010
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:35,430
Yan.

1011
00:35:35,870 --> 00:35:36,470
Who is it?

1012
00:35:36,910 --> 00:35:37,430
It's me.

1013
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:38,710
Coming, give me a sec.

1014
00:35:38,710 --> 00:35:39,840
I'm fixing my clothes.

1015
00:35:40,770 --> 00:35:41,870
Thought you'd fallen asleep.

1016
00:35:41,870 --> 00:35:42,760
Nope.

1017
00:35:45,150 --> 00:35:45,870
Tianyu.

1018
00:35:45,870 --> 00:35:46,520
Cooking time?

1019
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:47,080
Yeah.

1020
00:35:51,230 --> 00:35:52,520
What are you working on?

1021
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:54,280
Making the soup base.

1022
00:35:54,870 --> 00:35:55,950
The spicy hotpot broth?

1023
00:35:55,950 --> 00:35:56,870
The mild one first.

1024
00:35:58,120 --> 00:35:59,630
Then I'll make the spicy one.

1025
00:36:03,950 --> 00:36:05,080
Smells good?

1026
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:05,910
It's amazing.

1027
00:36:08,430 --> 00:36:09,840
We're adding tomatoes later, right?

1028
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:10,230
Right.

1029
00:36:10,230 --> 00:36:10,630
Slices?

1030
00:36:10,630 --> 00:36:11,630
Do you like them?

1031
00:36:12,100 --> 00:36:12,870
Should we cut them?

1032
00:36:12,870 --> 00:36:13,630
Yes.

1033
00:36:13,630 --> 00:36:14,320
How?

1034
00:36:16,870 --> 00:36:17,670
Let me handle it.

1035
00:36:18,630 --> 00:36:19,760
Here comes the chef.

1036
00:36:20,950 --> 00:36:22,080
The gentle chef.

1037
00:36:22,630 --> 00:36:23,390
It's showing up.

1038
00:36:24,390 --> 00:36:25,670
One tomato in four pieces, right?

1039
00:36:25,670 --> 00:36:26,280
Yeah.

1040
00:36:29,950 --> 00:36:31,360
Can I add the tomatoes now?

1041
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,120
Go ahead.

1042
00:36:32,120 --> 00:36:34,230
But I think it might have this issue.

1043
00:36:36,150 --> 00:36:36,950
A staged accident.

1044
00:36:38,560 --> 00:36:39,470
Let's cut another one.

1045
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:41,630
Sure.

1046
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:42,190
Is that okay?

1047
00:36:42,190 --> 00:36:42,910
Yeah.

1048
00:36:42,910 --> 00:36:43,870
Positive reinforcement?

1049
00:36:43,870 --> 00:36:45,430
Exactly.

1050
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:47,760
So, who's the chef today?

1051
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:48,080
You.

1052
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:49,840
It's always been you.

1053
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:51,630
I didn't really do much.

1054
00:36:51,630 --> 00:36:52,800
I just helped out a bit.

1055
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:53,570
Like an assistant?

1056
00:36:53,570 --> 00:36:54,080
Yeah.

1057
00:36:57,560 --> 00:36:58,570
No need to chop it finer,

1058
00:36:58,570 --> 00:36:59,280
Chef.

1059
00:37:00,150 --> 00:37:01,230
You think I'm praising you.

1060
00:37:01,230 --> 00:37:02,280
I'm saying it's done.

1061
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:03,950
You're totally being sarcastic.

1062
00:37:05,080 --> 00:37:06,250
It's starting to feel right.

1063
00:37:07,150 --> 00:37:07,950
Let me try a sip.

1064
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:12,520
Is it ready?

1065
00:37:12,520 --> 00:37:13,040
Yeah.

1066
00:37:13,040 --> 00:37:14,000
That's the flavor.

1067
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:15,720
Time to make Hot Chicken Flavor Ramen.

1068
00:37:22,470 --> 00:37:23,670
Wow, that's gentle.

1069
00:37:25,840 --> 00:37:28,000
You're seriously weird.

1070
00:37:33,520 --> 00:37:34,670
The water's not boiling yet.

1071
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:35,320
Yes.

1072
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:37,230
No, it's not boiling.

1073
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:38,710
It's fine. Put it in first.

1074
00:37:38,710 --> 00:37:39,600
Let it simmer slowly.

1075
00:37:40,120 --> 00:37:40,630
It'll work.

1076
00:37:40,630 --> 00:37:41,320
It's "dying".

1077
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:41,840
No way.

1078
00:37:41,840 --> 00:37:42,470
Already gone.

1079
00:37:42,470 --> 00:37:43,000
No way.

1080
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:43,530
"Die" again.

1081
00:37:43,530 --> 00:37:44,080
No way.

1082
00:37:44,080 --> 00:37:45,190
It's already been gone.

1083
00:37:45,190 --> 00:37:45,660
And again.

1084
00:37:45,660 --> 00:37:46,950
(Back from the brink)
Long gone.

1085
00:37:46,950 --> 00:37:47,360
And again.

1086
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:47,950
It's long gone.

1087
00:37:47,950 --> 00:37:48,630
No reincarnation.

1088
00:37:48,630 --> 00:37:49,320
Get chopsticks.

1089
00:37:49,320 --> 00:37:49,910
Get lost.

1090
00:37:59,630 --> 00:38:00,430
I'll do it.

1091
00:38:00,430 --> 00:38:02,000
You're way too slow.

1092
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:06,520
I'm speechless.

1093
00:38:06,520 --> 00:38:08,280
Then how fast are you?

1094
00:38:09,150 --> 00:38:10,190
About the same.

1095
00:38:10,430 --> 00:38:11,000
Don't act like

1096
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,520
you're amazing at this

1097
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:14,470
and I'm bad at this.

1098
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:15,670
Wipe this.

1099
00:38:21,910 --> 00:38:22,710
No oil, right?

1100
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:23,910
No oil.

1101
00:38:23,910 --> 00:38:25,560
I already washed my hands.

1102
00:38:28,870 --> 00:38:31,190
Let me do it.

1103
00:38:31,190 --> 00:38:31,950
Don't cut yourself.

1104
00:38:31,950 --> 00:38:33,870
I won't cut myself.

1105
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:36,280
These can't be used.

1106
00:38:36,710 --> 00:38:38,150
Then chop up all of these.

1107
00:38:38,150 --> 00:38:39,040
Why cut this?

1108
00:38:41,470 --> 00:38:43,040
Aren't these all unusable?

1109
00:38:43,040 --> 00:38:43,840
They're fine to use.

1110
00:38:44,870 --> 00:38:46,560
Just the ends can't be used.

1111
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,910
At least I can pour this sauce, right?

1112
00:38:54,910 --> 00:38:55,560
Yeah.

1113
00:39:00,430 --> 00:39:01,290
Let me twist it open.

1114
00:39:08,390 --> 00:39:10,190
Wow, impressive.

1115
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:17,870
I have to open at least one bottle.

1116
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:21,000
Oh, girl,

1117
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:23,470
can you?

1118
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,000
Let me do it.

1119
00:39:25,390 --> 00:39:26,360
You're cool.

1120
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:27,360
What?

1121
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:28,760
Jiayi, can you

1122
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:30,520
grab that plate for me?

1123
00:39:31,230 --> 00:39:32,390
Can you help me get that...

1124
00:39:32,390 --> 00:39:32,800
Get what?

1125
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:33,630
The slices

1126
00:39:33,630 --> 00:39:34,280
are too big.

1127
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:35,190
What is this?

1128
00:39:35,470 --> 00:39:36,470
Can you get this for me?

1129
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:42,390
I'll wash it.

1130
00:39:42,390 --> 00:39:43,190
Let me help.

1131
00:39:43,190 --> 00:39:44,600
This is all I can do right now.

1132
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:50,520
Do I need to cut this?

1133
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:52,600
What?

1134
00:39:52,600 --> 00:39:53,390
I'll do the cutting.

1135
00:39:53,710 --> 00:39:54,490
But yours are spicy.

1136
00:39:54,490 --> 00:39:55,320
And then you...

1137
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:56,600
Can you help me prepare sauce?

1138
00:39:56,600 --> 00:39:58,670
Just put a bit of each into the bowl.

1139
00:40:01,390 --> 00:40:03,190
Wanna give it a try?

1140
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:06,560
You've already bitten it.

1141
00:40:07,470 --> 00:40:09,000
It's not bad.

1142
00:40:09,870 --> 00:40:11,040
Yeah, I think it's good.

1143
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:11,870
Have some fruit.

1144
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:16,630
That's sour.

1145
00:40:16,630 --> 00:40:18,390
Some aren't that sour though.

1146
00:40:18,390 --> 00:40:19,280
Feed me one.

1147
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:21,080
That one's sweet.

1148
00:40:22,230 --> 00:40:23,080
I gave you one,

1149
00:40:23,080 --> 00:40:23,560
sour one.

1150
00:40:23,560 --> 00:40:24,560
Then she gave one

1151
00:40:24,560 --> 00:40:25,670
and it's so sweet?

1152
00:40:27,870 --> 00:40:29,050
They're sweet.

1153
00:40:29,050 --> 00:40:30,120
We all got the sweet ones.

1154
00:40:30,120 --> 00:40:30,600
Yeah.

1155
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:31,840
Nah, mine are always sour.

1156
00:40:32,190 --> 00:40:33,520
The ones you give me are sweet.

1157
00:40:35,950 --> 00:40:37,190
Do you really have to say that

1158
00:40:37,190 --> 00:40:37,800
in front of us?

1159
00:40:39,190 --> 00:40:40,280
Why that reaction?

